"Decode" is a song by Paramore released as a single from the soundtrack to the film Twilight. The song has been getting rotation on Los Angeles&#039;s huge radio station KIIS-FM. As of November 11, the single as been added to New York&#039;s Z100.

The official music video premiered on November 3, 2008 on MTVu, MTV, MTV2 and on MTV.com and was directed by Shane Drake. The video features the band members walking and performing in the woods, in Nashville, Tennessee. Scenes from Twilight are also intercut.

The song entered the U.S Billboard Hot Modern Rock Tracks at #35 and has peaked at #19, giving them their third top twenty hit on the chart. After one day of release, the song debuted at #15 and went on to peak at #12 on the U.S iTunes Chart. The song debuted on the Billboard Hot 100 at #34, the band&#039;s highest debut on the chart. It is their second top forty hit in the U.S., ending their one-hit wonder status in that country. In Canada it debuted at #52 on the Canadian Hot 100, also based on downloads.
